      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine) for construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod interface. Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error estimated at <1.2% for stiffness QoI and <2.8% for stress QoI. Fine mesh selected for production runs. Exceeds required Gradation 2 by providing quantified error bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
