      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-qoi-relevance",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the clinical performance concern of pedicle screw construct structural integrity under compressive-bending physiological loading. These QoIs are the standard regulatory endpoints for spinal implant bench clearance and are the quantities predicted by the FEA model in the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-va-relevance",
      "rationale": "The validation activity (ASTM F1717 bench test of N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm constructs across two laboratories) directly represents the COU: the same device design, same loading protocol, same QoIs, and same acceptance bounds used in the regulatory submission. No extrapolation of validation evidence beyond the tested configuration is required. The two-laboratory design provides inter-laboratory reproducibility data, strengthening the relevance assessment."
